# Changes

## v1.6.0 - 2026-07-09

- Redefined Quick, Standard, and Deep modes as Budget Profiles based on evidence depth, risk sampling strength, report length, subagent limits, and research intensity.
- Required each analysis to record budget targets and actual execution summaries without introducing exact token accounting or automatic token interruption.
- Updated the main workflow and subagent prompts so the selected mode drives Evidence Plan scope, evidence reading budget, risk sampling intensity, and report boundaries.
- Added a v1.6 manual acceptance checklist for comparing the same repository across Quick, Standard, and Deep modes.
- Updated user documentation to explain where extra analysis cost is spent and kept the workflow free of new CLI, JSON gate, or hard quality gate behavior.

## v1.5.0 - 2026-07-09

- Added Risk Sampling as a required core-module analysis step.
- Required each core module to sample at least one relevant risk path with object, source anchor, finding, and architecture impact.
- Documented risk categories including error handling, configuration loading, plugins/extension points, cache, concurrency, auth/security boundaries, and generated/vendor/test boundaries.
- Required non-applicable risk categories to be explained instead of silently omitted.
- Required final-report critical evaluation to cite risk sampling findings while keeping unsupported risk inferences subject to Unsupported Claims rules.
- Added a v1.5 manual acceptance checklist and updated user documentation without adding automatic risk scanners or a hard quality gate.

## v1.4.0 - 2026-07-09

- Added Unsupported Claims as a process-level final-report check for evidence status.
- Required core deterministic conclusions to carry source anchors, document evidence, or first-hand external sources.
- Required evidence-free judgments to move into assumptions, open questions, limitations, or unsupported areas.
- Kept cross-module inferences pending until main-agent verification, and prevented open questions from disappearing during synthesis.
- Added a v1.4 manual acceptance checklist focused on final-report behavior.
- Updated user documentation to describe verified vs unverified content without implying auto scanning, LLM judge, or a hard quality gate.

## v1.2.0 - 2026-07-09

- Added the Evidence Plan workflow to repo-analyzer module planning.
- Required each core module plan to state architecture questions, candidate entry points, required evidence types, risk paths, and expected judgment scope before subagent deep reading.
- Updated subagent guidance so module drafts answer their Evidence Plan and downgrade unsupported findings to limitations, assumptions, or open questions.
- Added a v1.2 manual acceptance checklist for validating Evidence Plan behavior.
- Updated user documentation to describe Evidence Plan as a lightweight Markdown planning-layer enhancement, without adding a CLI, JSON schema, Evidence Matrix, or hard quality gate.
